{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-15215/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-15215"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:52:15"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["exterior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Woman stands in the woods holding a brown basket"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-15215","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-15215"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1/22f67b1d-5ad3-4f13-b4bc-0728801d9c41","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:45:05.792Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma emerges from the bottom frame. Similar to the scenes in which characters’ rising upstairs signals variations in their class status and power dynamics among themselves, this motion likewise gives visual representation to Alma climbing out of her gloom after Reynolds’s vicious attack.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:309.680023923445,132.0798444976076,320.3827751196171,833.4285287081339"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1/46bb422d-4609-4f0a-927a-818f519ebfd0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:45:20.274Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma is associated with nature and the outside world from the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW62479676 BCX4\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-01537.html\"><u>start</u></a>. It is the source of her “art” of mushrooms and the control she wields in her relationship with Reynolds. Sima Movaghati offers a reading of the film that associates Alma with climbing ivy, which envelops itself around another being (a tree), produces poisonous berries that cause intestinal discomfort, and whose etymology can be linked to a form of possessive, obsessive love (Movaghati, “Bluebeard Meets Ivy,” 736).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15215/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:52.23534688995201,67.95753588516743,337.83642344497605,205.86423444976072"}}}]}]}]}